## Quick start

**macOS / Linux:**
```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<< github_repo_url | replace('https://github.com/', '') >>/main/install-<< project_slug >> | bash
```

**Windows (PowerShell):**
```powershell
irm https://raw.githubusercontent.com/<< github_repo_url | replace('https://github.com/', '') >>/main/install-<< project_slug >>.ps1 | iex
```

The installer will:
- Install [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) if needed
- Clone this repository
- Create a Python virtual environment
- Let you choose which documentation stacks to index
- Embed selected docs into a local ChromaDB vector store
- Auto-configure Claude Desktop and Claude Code

